3

) wider at base (
1.36 mm
) than long (
1.1 mm
); without carinae; impressions on disc (one deep longitudinal, median, from posterior to anterior margin); four gibbosities (two median, one on each side, on basal 
2
/ 
5
; two lateral, on each side, on basal 
4
/ 
9
); anterolateral angles rounded; concave at middle, extending over base of head; lateral margin feebly sinuate, smooth; posterior angles produced, acute; posterior margin with three arches, two broad, one on each side in front of elytron, and one narrow in front of scutellum. Elytra (

Fig. 
3

) subparallel; longer (
2.88 mm
