) long, robust; pro- and mesocoxae globular; protibiae with two (anterior and internal margins) short fringes of tomentum on apices; meso- and metatibiae with one (internal margin) short fringe of tomentum on apices; last tarsal segment longer than remaining segments combined; tarsal claws without basal teeth.

Abdomen (
Fig. 4
